GOAL: make a live-captured NIGHTSHIFT episode BYTE-COMPATIBLE with a curated
ep.k by capturing it through the SAME batched gemma4_decode_cuda + SP_XBAR_RECALL_WRITE
path the curator used, so the DEPLOYED W_c head works on it with ZERO retraining.
Prior failure (eac4106): per-token gemma4_kv_prefill+read_global_k provenance =>
K norm ~half + scrambled direction => live episode SUPER-ATTRACTED (~41) => foreign
reject failed.

FILES CHANGED
  tools/sp_daemon/c_backend_cuda/sp_daemon_cuda_glue.c
     + sp_daemon_cuda_kvcapture_batched(qm, tokens, n, out_dir):
       extern gemma4_decode_cuda; _putenv_s SP_XBAR_RECALL_WRITE=out_dir;
       gemma4_decode_cuda(qm, seq, n, n_gen=0, eos=1); unset env.
       NOTE: gemma4_decode_cuda returns the valid token count (n_prompt) on
       SUCCESS, -1 on error -> glue normalizes (rc<0)?-1:0.
