ROOT CAUSE of the residual gap (curated 9.858 vs live 0.084 on IDENTICAL text):
  a 2-token TOKENIZATION mismatch between the curator (sp_tok_enc) and the live
  B4-NIGHTSHIFT capture (routes.rs). The curated ep.tok for ep_n_div_000 is:
    2 1437 2481 6980 2442 236772 57890 79744 114947 580 236743 236778 236772 \
    25862 7218 236772 236825 236812 236778 236828 236761 107        (npos=22)
  tok[0]=2 is the gemma4 FORCED BOS; tok[-1]=107 is the trailing-newline token
  (the curator captured each needle from a .txt file ending in '\n', so the
  encoder emitted the newline piece). The live path did the OPPOSITE on BOTH
  boundaries: it called encode(text.trim()) (no trailing '\n' -> no 107) AND
  then explicitly stripped the BOS ("if toks.first()==Some(&2){toks.remove(0)}").
  Result: npos=20, a DIFFERENT token stream -> a DIFFERENT ep.k -> W_c score
  collapse (live 0.084 vs curated 9.858).

FIX 1 (routes.rs B4-NIGHTSHIFT, step (a)): byte-match the curator EXACTLY —
  encode format!("{text}\n") (append the trailing newline) and KEEP the forced
  BOS (removed the toks.remove(0) line). Live capture now yields npos=22 with the
  same ids as the curator.

FIX 2 (cuda_forward.cu ~L3714): the SP_XBAR_RECALL_WRITE writer was gated by a
  process-static "static int xbar_written" write-once guard. The curator is a
  fresh process per needle so it never tripped; the resident daemon is ONE
  long-lived process, so ep_live_000 wrote and every later live capture
  (ep_live_001+) silently skipped -> load_episode_global_k -> None. Replaced the
  guard with an unconditional write each call (the WRITE path keys on the
  freshly set+unset out_dir). SELFTEST/LOAD paths untouched. Verified: ep_live_001
  now writes on the 2nd same-boot capture.

BUILD: _b3v9_rebuild.bat (cmake CUDA backend lib: cuda_forward.cu recompiled
  -> sp_cuda_daemon_backend.lib) + cargo --features wire_cuda_backend -> sp-daemon.
  0 errors. B3V9_BUILD_OK.
  (Also restored sp_daemon_cuda_glue.c from HEAD — its working-tree copy was a
   prior-session mount-truncation casualty ending in a stray 'c'; not part of
   this change, just un-broke the build.)

