VERDICT (B): HEAD-GENERALIZATION LIMIT (honest negative).
  The provenance fix WORKS — the novel live episode is now fully IN-BAND
  (T2 6.295, not the old super-collapse; correctly rejected at -15.498 on the
  foreign query). BUT the deployed W_c head is a CLOSED-SET instance selector
  over the 90 curated div needles: on the novel fact's own query a curated
  needle (ep_n_div_021=7.830, a same-archetype 'key/code' instance) OUT-RANKS the
  novel live episode (6.295, rank 18/92). The head learned per-instance
  prototypes for the trained corpus; an UNSEEN novel instance lands mid-pack, not
  #1. So NIGHTSHIFT's machinery is end-to-end correct (capture -> byte-exact
  provenance -> in-band scoring -> foreign-reject), but autonomous recall of a
  GENUINELY NOVEL live fact needs a GENERAL-RELEVANCE head (not the closed-set
  instance head), exactly as pre-scoped.

  novel-live vs winning-curated:  6.295  vs  7.830   (gap 1.535 nats, novel loses)
  novel-live foreign-reject:      -15.498  (clean reject, NULL wins)

DEFAULT-OFF NULL FLOOR: SP_B4_NIGHTSHIFT unset => the whole hook is skipped
